,"It is located between the sphenoid and temporal bones"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elambdoid suture\u003C/strong\u003E, named for its resemblance to the Greek letter lambda (\u039b), is located between the parietal bones and the occipital bone of the skull. This suture is one of several fibrous joints that connect the bones of the skull, allowing for growth during development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecoronal suture\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the frontal and parietal bones, not the lambdoid suture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esquamosal suture\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the temporal and parietal bones, which is different from the lambdoid suture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efrontonasal suture\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the frontal and nasal bones, not involving the lambdoid suture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenosquamosal suture\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the sphenoid and temporal bones, which is not related to the lambdoid suture.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The lambdoid suture is located between the parietal bones and the occipital bone of the skull.","Sutures are the fibrous joints that connect the bones of the skull.","The lambdoid suture is named for its resemblance to the Greek letter lambda (\u039b)."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64149"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17946"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64149","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64149"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T18:56:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T20:04:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10660"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78800"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4904","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4904"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Neuroanatomy","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-13T23:02:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-13T23:02:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"10"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"